  "prompt": "Why does my girlfriend of 7 years dont reply to my text or calls when she says that it wont be long. what should I do?",
  "response": "It\u2019s understandable to feel worried or frustrated when your partner is not responsive. Here are a few steps you might consider:\n\n1. **Give It Some Time:** Sometimes people can be genuinely busy or caught up in situations that make them less responsive. If she says that it won\u2019t be long, consider giving her some space and time.\n\n2. **Talk About It:** Once she\u2019s available, have an open and honest conversation about how you\u2019re feeling. Express your concerns calmly and listen to her perspective. Communication is key in understanding each other's needs and expectations.\n\n3. **Evaluate Patterns:** If this happens frequently, it might be helpful to evaluate if there is a pattern or specific circumstances where she becomes unresponsive. This can give you insights into any underlying issues that might need attention.\n\n4. **Seek Understanding:** Try to understand the reasons behind her unresponsiveness. Is she going through a stressful period, dealing with personal issues, or just needing some alone time? Understanding the context can help you respond appropriately.\n\n5. **Consider Her Perspective:** Reflect on whether there might be external factors or reasons beyond her control that might be affecting her ability to respond promptly.\n\n6. **Set Boundaries:** Discuss and set mutual expectations regarding communication. Finding a balance that works for both of you can reduce misunderstandings and anxiety.\n\nRemember, effective communication and understanding each other's needs are fundamental to a healthy relationship.",
